                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d422">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.032/45: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-07T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 7, 1920—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>44. Your April 2, 1 a.m., and March 23, 11 a.m.</p>
                <p>If the question is still a live one, and the Department’s opinion desired, you
                    may state that the Department believes the proposed law might have an
                    unfortunate and disquieting effect, particularly upon foreign investors in
                    Peru.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
